# Difference Between next() and nextLine()

| next() | nextLine() |
|---------|------------|
| Reads one word | Reads the entire line |
| Stops at whitespace (space, tab, newline) | Reads until Enter is pressed |
| Cannot read a full sentence | Can read a full sentence |

---

# Example using next()

```java
Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

String name = sc.next();

System.out.println(name);
```

Input

```
Krishna Priya
```

Output

```
Krishna
```

Reason

`next()` stops reading when it encounters whitespace.

---

# Example using nextLine()

```java
Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

String name = sc.nextLine();

System.out.println(name);
```

Input

```
Krishna Priya
```

Output

```
Krishna Priya
```

Reason

`nextLine()` reads the entire line until the Enter key is pressed.

